  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Server*. Using *JIRA Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRACLOUD-8754].
  {panel}

Maybe I am missing something, but it seems that custom screens must always present the comment field.  In other words, if I create a custom screen with fields A, B, and C, when that screen is displayed, I will see fields A, B, C, and Comment(s).  I would like to be able to selectively disable the comment(s) field.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Server*. Using *JIRA Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRACLOUD-8753].
  {panel}

Is it possible to simply display custom text (HTML) in a custom screen?  In my particular case, I don't want people using the Edit Operation.  Instead, I provide edit screens within the workflow.  So, I would like to create a screen that simply says "Use the Edit function in the workflow." in big letters, and then map that screen via the Screen Scheme to the Edit Operation.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Server*. Using *JIRA Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRACLOUD-8751].
  {panel}

During the Log Work Done operation, TIME SPENT field is mandatory but the Work Description field is not. 
It would be very nice to have this capability mandatory, if not configurable w.r.t.the contexts/projects: because those informations are so important that developers could not skip them, if they want to.

The following:
{noformat}
{count:<dataset-ID>}
{noformat}

will get rendered as:
{count:<dataset-ID>}

It thinks the the contents of the angle brackets is an html tag.  (view the source of above and you will see the tag)

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Server*. Using *JIRA Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRACLOUD-8720].
  {panel}

In the screen layout, it would be nice to have the ability to place more than one field per line and also the possiblity to draw a table in which the user can put values in (without the use of a renderer).

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Server*. Using *JIRA Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRACLOUD-8717].
  {panel}

When progressing an issue through a workflow, specifically closing the issue;

jiraSoapService.progressWorkflowAction(soapTaken, issueKey, "2", actionParams);

I observed that any values not *explictly* listed in the action Params list, but shown on the Resolve screen, were cleared of their values. In particuarly, I had several custom fields that were mysteriously disappearing.  It took me quite a while to figure out why simply closing a workflow item was automatically clearing out unrelated fields out from under me!

Nick Menere suggested I submit an Feature Request stating that values should retain their current values unless specifically modified.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Server*. Using *JIRA Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRACLOUD-8709].
  {panel}

At the moment JIra stores all the issues in memory, deletes and reindexes one-by-one.

We should investigate ways to make this use less memory, we should use the same method that Delete Project does.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Server*. Using *JIRA Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRACLOUD-8702].
  {panel}

JIRA's HTML emails use the default colours regardless of how JIRA's look & feel settings are configured.  We should optionally allow custom colours to be used.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Server*. Using *JIRA Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRACLOUD-8697].
  {panel}

I have a need to create a one to many type of field.  We want to use JIRA to track Problem Logs, just like it is supposed to do.  I want the developer to be able to add the modules that were fixed for the issue.  There could be many of these for each issue.  There doesn't appear to be any custom field of this type to add.  It is almost like the comments and worklog, where you log that in a hangoff table in order to preserve the one to many aspect of it.  This custom field type would probably get stored in the same table as comments and worklogs.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Server*. Using *JIRA Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRACLOUD-8695].
  {panel}

If the "reporter" field is modified when submitting a new issue, it's not possible in JIRA UI to find who have actually submitted the issue.

Is it possible to add a record about the issue creation to the issue history?

see also JRA-761

