{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This suggestion is for *JIRA Server*. Using *JIRA Cloud*? [See the corresponding suggestion|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRACLOUD-8683].
  {panel}

The way I do some upgrades is to get the new version of JIRA running on the same machine, but on a different port. I then import the data from the running JIRA and test it out before making the switch. The problem is that an import seems to include the index directory, which then sets the second JIRA instance to index in the old directory, which corrupts the index of the running JIRA. There should be an option on import to exclude the settings for the index/attachements/backups directories.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
